.TH "svc_rdma_listen_handler" 9 "svc_rdma_listen_handler" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
svc_rdma_listen_handler \- Handle CM events generated on a listening endpoint
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" svc_rdma_listen_handler
.BI "(struct rdma_cm_id *cma_id "  ","
.BI "struct rdma_cm_event *event "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cma_id" 12
the server's listener rdma_cm_id
.IP "event" 12
details of the event
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return values:
0: Do not destroy \fIcma_id\fP
1: Destroy \fIcma_id\fP (never returned here)

NB: There is never a DEVICE_REMOVAL event for INADDR_ANY listeners.
